  "title": "n8n SQL injection in MySQL, PostgreSQL, and Microsoft SQL database nodes",
  "description": "The MySQL, PostgreSQL, and Microsoft SQL database nodes in n8n build parts of SQL queries from workflow-controlled configuration without consistently validating or safely escaping those fragments. In the vulnerable snapshot, MySQL and PostgreSQL interpolate unvalidated where-clause operators into SQL, MySQL also interpolates sort direction directly into ORDER BY, and the Microsoft SQL node concatenates unescaped identifier fields into SELECT, UPDATE, and DELETE queries. An authenticated user with workflow editing permissions can inject arbitrary SQL through crafted node configuration.",
